Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reportShield(25.10)                                        reportShield(25.10)

Name
       reportShield - Reports shield coverage for nets routed by the NanoRoute
       router

Syntax
       reportShield

       [-help]

       [-crosstie]

       [-include_layer]

       [-out_file <fileName>]

       [-selected]

       [-tap_cells]

       [-verbose]

       Reports  shield  coverage  for  nets routed by the NanoRoute router. It
       provides information on the shielding  effectiveness  across  different
       layers.  The  report includes details of the expected and actual shield
       coverage, percentage  coverage,  pre-route  shield  coverage,  and  the
       power-to-ground ratio across different layers.

       Note: This command works on the NanoRoute database. If the user enables
       setNanoRouteMode  -route_selected_net_only,  the  reportShield  command
       only reports shield ratio of selected nets.

Parameters
       -crosstie
              Reports the shield coverage of all shielded nets  with  crosstie
              attributes.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each reportShield parameter. For  a  detailed  de-
              scription  of the command and all of its parameters, use the man
              command: man reportShield.

       -include_layer
              Reports the shielding ratio per layer per net in addition to the
              ratio for the whole net.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -out_file <fileName>
              Specifies the report file name.

              Default: <designName>_shield.rpt

              Data_type: string, optional

       -selected
              Reports statistics for selected nets only.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -tap_cells
              Generates a separate report file with tapping details  for  each
              net,  including  the  tap cell name, instance name, and instance
              coordinates. If a tapping distance violation occurs, it is  also
              included in the report.

              Note:      The      tapping      report     file     name     is
              <cell_name>_<view_name>_shield_tapping_<time_stamp>.rpt.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -verbose
              Includes a list of nets that are  skipped,  which  includes  the
              following nets:

              * FIXED nets

              * SPECIAL nets

              * Nets with the skip_routing attribute

              * Nets with opens

              Data_type: bool, optional

Examples
       The  following  command  reports for selected nets only but breaks them
       down by segment. The summary report will be printed  in  log,  and  de-
       tailed report will be in myDesign_shield.rpt file.

       reportShield -crosstie -selected -verbose -out_file myDesign_shield.rpt

       In myDesign_shield.rpt file:

       NET in:

       +-----------------------------+------------+------------+----------+------------+-----------+--------+--------------+

       |  Segment                      |  Layer name | Expected # | Actual # |
       Percentage | Pre-route | Shield | Power:Ground |

       +-----------------------------+------------+------------+----------+------------+-----------+--------+--------------+

       | 0.1600 4.8960 2.9120 4.8960 | metal1     | 42         | 0        | 0%
       | 0         | 0      | 0:0          |

       | 0.1600 4.8960 2.9120 4.8960 | metal3     | 28          |  11        |
       39%        | 0         | 11     | 0:11         |

       +-----------------------------+------------+------------+----------+------------+-----------+--------+--------------+

       |  Total                        |             | 70         | 11       |
       15%        | 0         | 11     | 0:11         |

       +-----------------------------+------------+------------+----------+------------+-----------+--------+--------------+

       In the log file:

       #Crosstie Table:

